        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18257",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When you say \"inside an action\", do you mean inside an action controller method? I need more context.\n\nThe action() view helper by itself does not act as a placeholder, it simply returns content; as such, if you want it to appear in the layout script, you need to either put it in a placeholder, or include it in content that will be aggregated into the layout.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-09T15:12:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-09T15:12:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18260",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sidhighwind",
                        "name": "sidhighwind",
                        "displayName": "Jon Whitcraft",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok here is what i do.\n\ni request a page lets say http:\/\/test.com\/news\/story\/My_Story\n\nIn my setup that would make it Module of news controller of story and the defualt index action as My_Story is the title of the story which is how I know which story to fetch from the db.  inside of the index action i call get the story and assign it to a view.\n\ninside of my view script i have the code to out put the story.\n\nat the bottom of the view script i call this code.\n\n{code}\n<?= $this->action('index', 'news', 'talkback', array('story_id' => $this->story->release_id)) ?>\n{code}\n\nwhich call the talkback module news controller index action which if talkback exists for the passed in release then it will spit out the necessary code for the talkback module on the page.\n\nThe way i think this should work is that i should beable to specify any addition css\/js\/meta data that is needed in that action even though it's begin call through the action helper.\n\nDoest that make sense?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sidhighwind",
                        "name": "sidhighwind",
                        "displayName": "Jon Whitcraft",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-09T19:08:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-09T19:08:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18667",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When you say \"inside of my view script\", is this the view script rendered for the action, or your layout script?\n\nIf the call to $this->action() is occurring in your layout script, then this won't work; it's being executed *after* the other helpers have already created their output. If it's happening in your view script, but *before* the layout script is rendered, then there's a definite issue.\n\nCould you confirm the sequence of events?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-29T14:13:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-29T14:13:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/18682",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sidhighwind",
                        "name": "sidhighwind",
                        "displayName": "Jon Whitcraft",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "it it called from the action and not the layout.\n\nso i call $this->render('designs') at the end of an action to render the designs.phtml for the current module.  Inside side of that i have the $this->action('design_nav','navigation','designid', array()) call to render the local navigation or some other piece of this page.  but when i try add scripts or css files from that action they do not get added.\n\ndoes that make sense?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sidhighwind",
                        "name": "sidhighwind",
                        "displayName": "Jon Whitcraft",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-01-29T15:02:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-01-29T15:02:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
